reviewText: This really is a nicely done collection of Alicia Keys with both the DVD to view on a TV and the CD for the music. The quality and sound of the DVD is very good.  I like the arrangement on this, and Girl on Fire is especially good.  I can see viewing this over and over for many years.
If you already like her music, this is right up your alley.  She makes the audience feel like she's a personal friend.  She talks about her motivations for some of her songs.  All in all a winner

I first watched and recorded this fine concert on the "Story Tellers" program almost a year ago.  This is a great series that showcases contemporary artists in a small studio setting (similar to HBO's "Unplugged" concert series), and they could not have chosen a better performer for this venue than Alicia Keys.  Alicia performs approximately 10 songs, each of which are preceded with pertinent commentary about the background and/or inspiration for the composition.  She performs a diverse collection of her popular songs, some from the most recent album, and several hits from previous recordings, and it all combines to provide a concert-worthy presentation that all of her fans (and any newbies) will thoroughly enjoy.  As such, I was ecstatic when I discovered that this great performance was being issued on DVD so that I can have a copy to play many times in the future.  And, as an added bonus, the DVD includes several songs and that were not included in the television show, which makes this DVD a MUST HAVE for anyone who loves great R&B music !!!
